egory\":\"functionality\",\"title\":\"Add database connectivity to health endpoint\",\"description\":\"The /health endpoint reports worker count and OAuth token status but does not verify database availability. Add a lightweight SQLite pragma check (e.g., PRAGMA quick_check on a small table or SELECT 1) for the main database and report it in the health response. If tenantDbManager is available, include a count of accessible tenant databases. This makes database failures detectable via health checks before they surface as 500 errors.\",\"reasoning\":\"If a tenant database becomes corrupted or the SQLite file is locked, the health endpoint still returns ok. Operators and load balancers cannot distinguish a healthy node from one that will fail on every request. Adding DB health closes the most critical blind spot in the current health check.\",\"status\":\"pending\",\"user_feedback\":null,\"user_pattern\":0,\"effort\":2,\"impact\":7,\"implemented_at\":null,\"created_at\":\"2026-03-18T11:51:14.642Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-18T11:51:14.642Z\",\"requirement_id\":null,\"goal_id\":null,\"risk\":2,\"provider\":null,\"model\":null,\"detailed\":0}}","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
